Cell[TextData[{
 "This notebook provides symbolic expressions of short-distance coefficients \
(SDCs) used in the calculation of fragmentation functions (FFs) into fully \
heavy tetraquarks ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["T", 
     RowBox[{"4", "Q"}]], "(", 
    SuperscriptBox["J", 
     StyleBox["PC",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "54a1a962-5cd1-4e6d-abb8-903c9d6f710f"],
 "  [T2, T1a, T1b, T0]. \nThe expressions are extracted from the internal \
symbolic framework ",
 StyleBox["symJETHAD",
  FontFamily->"Courier New",
  FontWeight->"Regular"],
 " [J1-J7] and correspond to: \n- Gluon and heavy-quark fragmentation \
channels\n- Spin-parity assignments ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["J", 
    StyleBox["PC",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "43bebe2b-c571-4a77-a741-e37317663b9f"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["0", "++"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "579a4a14-26ee-471c-81a4-66f6e72745d9"],
 " (scalar), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["1", 
    RowBox[{"+", "-"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4aadec1e-79db-454d-92f8-966b9deb015d"],
 " (axial vector), 2",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["", "++"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c989e0ba-61c9-4642-b162-9bf75778f318"],
 " (tensor)\n- NRQCD operators [n] = [3, 3], [6, 6], [3, 6]\n\nAll results \
are obtained at leading order (LO) in the strong coupling ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "s"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "790f0b97-7f13-4f9f-811f-0d91b985698d"],
 ", and assume massless initial-state partons . \nNRQCD LDMEs must be \
provided externally and multiplied to the SDCs as indicated in the manuscript \
. \nThe notebook is self-contained and ready for symbolic manipulation or \
numerical evaluation ."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.965110726126541*^9, 3.965110933950754*^9}, {
  3.965116381174953*^9, 3.96511639821189*^9}, {3.965117110583984*^9, 
